Name: Data Consumer Wallet
Description: This is the wallet address that pays for the query fees.

Name: Amount paid
Description: What the customer has already paid.

Name: Amount remaining
Description: What the customer will pay in the future.

Name: Total cost
Description: The total value in US dollars of the offering.

Name: Total Gateway Query Fees Billed GRT
Total Gateway Query Fees Billed USD
Billing Balance
Description: The balance of GRT in the billing contact for the Studio User

Name: Chains Published to
Description: The chains that a Studio User has published subgraphs to.
Options: Arbitrum; Avalanche; Base; BSC; Celo; Fantom; Linea; Mainnet; Optimism; Scroll; Solana; Polygon; Arbitrum Sepolia; Gnosis; Moonriver

Name: Consumer Lifespan Days
Description: The number of days a Data Consumer Wallet has been a customer.

Name: Current Signaled Tokens
Description: The sum of all the tokens is currently signaled to a studio user's subgraphs.

Name: Data Consumer Org Name
Description: The Organization Name for the Data Consumer Wallet

Name: Category
Description: A drop down or multi-select field where customers can differentiate among varied offerings i.e. Marketing hub onboarding vs. full suite onboarding, etc.
Options: Marketing Hub onboarding (marketing_hub_onboarding); Full Suite onboarding (full_suite_onboarding)

Name: Close date
Description: Date the record is "closed".

Name: Created by user ID
Description: The user who created this record. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.

Name: Object create date/time
Description: The date and time at which this object was created. This value is automatically set by HubSpot and may not be modified.

Name: Description
Description: An explanation of the offering that is being represented

Name: Object last modified date/time
Description: Most recent timestamp of any property update for this object. This includes HubSpot internal properties, which can be visible or hidden. This property is updated automatically.

Name: Merged record IDs
Description: The list of record IDs that have been merged into this record. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.

Name: Name
Description: Short-summary of the offering the record represents.

Name: Record ID
Description: The unique ID for this record. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.

Name: Record source detail 1
Description: First level of detail on how this record was created.

Name: Record source detail 2
Description: Second level of detail on how this record was created.

Name: Record source detail 3
Description: Third level of detail on how this record was created.

Name: Record source
Description: How this record was created.

Name: Pipeline
Description: The pipeline that contains this service

Name: Pipeline Stage
Description: The pipeline stage that contains this service

Name: Start date
Description: Date the offering starts being worked on by either the customer or the company

Name: Status
Description: This represents how the project is tracking relative towards expectations.

Name: Tags
Description: Deal tags associated with your service.

Name: Target end date
Description: Date the offering is anticipated to be completed.

Name: Updated by user ID
Description: The user who last updated this record. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.

Name: Owner assigned date
Description: The most recent timestamp of when an owner was assigned to this record. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.

Name: Owner
Description: The owner of the object.

Name: Owner's main team
Description: The main team of the record owner. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.

Name: Mainnet Website
Description: The website a studio user has listed in their profile.

Name: Network Num Failed Queries
Description: This is the number of failed queries on the decentralized network.

Name: Network Num Queries
Description: This is the total number of decentralized network queries, including failed queries.

Name: Number of Subgraphs
Description: The number of subgraphs associated with a Studio User's wallet address.

Name: Registered Email Addresses
Description: The email addresses added to the Studio User account.

Name: Studio Org Name
Description: This is the name of the organization provided by the user in the Studio account.
